= Operations and Setup =

== Solution Characteristics ==
* Target framework family: .NET Framework 4.7.2
* Main run surfaces: Pulse.Web and Pulse.Api
* Oracle-backed persistence via managed Oracle provider and Dapper

== Configuration Areas ==
Review application configuration files for:
* DB connection strings
* JWT settings
* Active Directory integration settings
* SMTP settings
* SSO logout redirect settings

== Deployment Considerations ==
* Keep Jwt:* values synchronized where token minting and validation occur.
* Validate module claim issuance aligns with MODULES and access-right assignments.
* Ensure Oracle schema permissions cover both read and mutation workloads used by services.

== Common Troubleshooting Notes ==
=== API Calls Authenticated with JWT ===
If GET works but POST/PUT/DELETE returns 401, inspect request-specific AJAX hooks that might override token headers.

=== Project Creation Scope ===
Plant/product/roadmap lookup endpoints should be membership-scoped to current user context.

=== Empty Plant Selection Edge ===
Guard client calls that depend on selected plant code to avoid noisy or invalid lookup requests.

== Suggested Validation Checklist ==
# Confirm login, token minting, and authenticated API call path
# Confirm module-claim-protected routes block/allow correctly
# Confirm plant/project membership scope is enforced
# Confirm notifications unread/grouped/read flows work end-to-end
# Confirm roadmap snapshot, insertion, and sync scenarios

